S1901M Negotiation summary: EAS has not made any prior moves in this round, focusing on negotiation and alliance-building with MID and WES.
EAS has engaged in three subrounds of negotiations with MID and WES. The discussions centered on forming strategic alliances to secure unowned supply centers like BRE and MOO. EAS proposed coordinated attacks, with WES suggesting a joint push to secure these centers. MID agreed to assist in MOO and provide logistical support. All parties have agreed to share intelligence and ensure mutual benefit, with a commitment to counter any betrayals.

S1901M Intent going forward: EAS intends to execute the agreed-upon joint attacks on BRE and MOO. EAS will coordinate with WES to secure BRE using units in FRA and SAX, while MID will assist in MOO via TUS and TRA. EAS will ensure intelligence sharing and maintain vigilance against potential betrayals. The focus is on securing supply centers and strengthening the alliance through coordinated military actions.

S1901M Negotiation summary: No prior moves have been recorded in the negotiation history.
MID has engaged in three subrounds of negotiations with EAS and WES. In the first subround, MID expressed interest in expanding influence in the Mediterranean and sought alliances. EAS and WES responded with openness to cooperation, particularly in securing unowned supply centers. In the second subround, MID proposed coordinated attacks on CRO and PAP, and WES suggested mutual support in securing key territories. In the third subround, MID formalized a strategic alliance with both EAS and WES to attack unowned supply centers, with clear roles and commitments. All parties confirmed their support, agreeing to share intelligence and mutual defense.

S1901M Intent going forward: MID intends to execute the finalized alliance plan, with EAS handling BRE, WES handling MOO, and MID providing logistical support. The alliance will focus on securing unowned supply centers through coordinated attacks. MID will ensure intelligence sharing and mutual defense against common threats. Any betrayal will be addressed through countermeasures. The goal is to maximize territorial gains and strengthen MID's position in the Mediterranean.

S1901M Negotiation summary: No prior moves have been recorded in the negotiation history.
WES has engaged in three subrounds of negotiations with EAS and MID. Initial missives proposed strategic alliances to secure supply centers BRE and MOO. EAS and MID expressed interest in cooperation but emphasized mutual benefit. In the second subround, WES proposed coordinated attacks on BRE and MOO, with EAS supporting NEU and MID assisting in TRA. EAS confirmed commitment to joint operations, while MID agreed to formalize an alliance. The third subround finalized the plan, with all parties agreeing to share intelligence and ensure mutual defense. No promises were broken, and all parties remain neutral or in early alliance stages.

S1901M Intent going forward: WES intends to execute the coordinated attacks on BRE and MOO as planned. EAS will support WES in NEU, and MID will assist in TRA. WES will share intelligence with both allies and ensure that all operations are synchronized to prevent betrayal. The goal is to secure key supply centers and strengthen the alliance with EAS and MID.
